## Data Usage Rules

All calculations must use values from the Data Package. Only use defaults if Data Package shows "NOT FOUND":

| Data Point | Use From Data Package | Default If Missing |
|------------|----------------------|-------------------|
| Valuations (CAPE, P/E) | VALUATIONS table | Cannot proceed without |
| Dividend yields | VALUATIONS table (Div Yield column) | US 1.3%, EU 2.8%, JP 2.0%, EM 2.5% |
| Volatility | VOLATILITY table ("Use for Merton" column) | US 16%, EU 18%, JP 20%, EM 22%, Gold 15% |
| Risk-free rate | RATES section | 2.5% |
| Thresholds | SUGGESTED THRESHOLDS table | See defaults below |
| Bond position | USER-PROVIDED DATA section | Exclude from calcs if missing |

**Default Thresholds (only if not in Data Package):**
| Region | Cautious If | Favorable If |
|--------|-------------|--------------|
| US | CAPE > 35 OR fwd P/E > 22 | CAPE < 25 |
| Europe | fwd P/E > 16 | fwd P/E < 14 |
| Japan | CAPE > 25 | CAPE < 18 |
| EM | fwd P/E > 14 | fwd P/E < 13 |

